@startuml C4_L2_Container_Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam titleFontSize 22
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
}
skinparam database {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFF4CC
}

title C4 Level 2 - Container Diagram\nTicketing Microservices System

actor "Client\n(Postman / Browser / Frontend)" as Client

rectangle "API Gateway\nSpring Boot" as Gateway

rectangle "Customers Service\nSpring Boot :8081" as Customers
rectangle "Event Service\nSpring Boot :8082" as Events
rectangle "Ticket Inventory Service\nSpring Boot :8083" as Inventory
rectangle "Ticket Order Management Service\nSpring Boot :8084" as Orders

database "customers-db\nH2" as CustomersDB
database "event-db\nH2" as EventsDB
database "ticketinventory-db\nH2" as InventoryDB
database "ticketordermanagement-db\nH2" as OrdersDB

Client --> Gateway : REST API requests
Gateway --> Customers : /api/customers/**
Gateway --> Events : /api/events/**
Gateway --> Inventory : /api/ticket-inventories/**
Gateway --> Orders : /api/ticket-orders/**

Customers --> CustomersDB : JPA / Flyway
Events --> EventsDB : JPA / Flyway
Inventory --> InventoryDB : JPA / Flyway
Orders --> OrdersDB : JPA / Flyway

Orders ..> Customers : validates customer eligibility\nCustomerEligibilityRestAdapter
Orders ..> Events : validates event eligibility\nEventEligibilityRestAdapter
Orders ..> Inventory : validates ticket inventory eligibility\nTicketInventoryEligibilityRestAdapter

note bottom of Orders
Order service coordinates the purchase flow.
It keeps references to customer, event,
and inventory instead of owning their data.
end note
@enduml
